<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDB8B025E8FF8E422A8F838" bold="true" box="[189,457,1910,1936]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFDB8B035E8FF83720B7FEC1" blockId="40.[189,1401,1957,2018]" lastBlockId="41.[189,1399,265,362]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDB8B025E8FF8372149F817" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,552,1957,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippopotamorum" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDB8B025E8FF8372149F817" box="[189,552,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Ebenacobius hippopotamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFDB8B025C07F837218DF817" box="[565,748,1957,1983]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by the following combination of features: claws simple, prothorax with two dark bands on each side of the median line, reaching the basal and apical margins of prothorax and elytra with minute setae glabrous in appearance (
<figureCitation id="13222A4FFFDA8B035AFCFE9B264DFE8B" box="[1230,1324,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1853,1879]" captionTargetBox="[377,1222,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-15@20.[349,1238,265,1815]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 3. A–I. Habitus of males of Ebenacobius Haran gen. nov. in dorsal view (part 2). A. E. mulanjensis Haran gen. et sp. nov. B. E. hessei Haran gen. et sp. nov. C. E. pedi Haran gen. et sp. nov. D. E. tsonga Haran gen. et sp. nov. E. E. hippopotamorum Haran gen. et sp. nov. F. E. incognitus (Hesse, 1929) gen. et comb. nov. G. E. oberprieleri Haran gen. et sp. nov. H. E. turneri (Marshall, 1935) gen. et comb. nov. I. E. rhodesianus (Hesse, 1929) gen. et comb. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6532977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6532977/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDA8B035C38FEBF213EFEEE" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[522,607,300,326]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedi" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDA8B035C38FEBF213EFEEE" box="[522,607,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">E. pedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFDA8B035C55FEBF207AFEEF" box="[615,795,301,327]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDA8B035D66FEBF20A5FEEE" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[852,964,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsonga" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDA8B035D66FEBF20A5FEEE" box="[852,964,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">E. tsonga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFDA8B035DFCFEBF27E1FEEF" box="[974,1152,301,327]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but in these species bands on prothorax are not reaching the apical margin (
<figureCitation id="13222A4FFFDA8B035D75FEDD20A8FEC1" box="[839,969,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1853,1879]" captionTargetBox="[377,1222,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-15@20.[349,1238,265,1815]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 3. A–I. Habitus of males of Ebenacobius Haran gen. nov. in dorsal view (part 2). A. E. mulanjensis Haran gen. et sp. nov. B. E. hessei Haran gen. et sp. nov. C. E. pedi Haran gen. et sp. nov. D. E. tsonga Haran gen. et sp. nov. E. E. hippopotamorum Haran gen. et sp. nov. F. E. incognitus (Hesse, 1929) gen. et comb. nov. G. E. oberprieleri Haran gen. et sp. nov. H. E. turneri (Marshall, 1935) gen. et comb. nov. I. E. rhodesianus (Hesse, 1929) gen. et comb. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6532977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6532977/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3036541FFDA8B035E8FFE032616FE54" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFDA8B035E8FFE032225FE03" blockId="41.[189,324,401,427]" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFDA8B035E8FFE032225FE03" bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDA8B035E8FFE032225FE03" bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFDA8B035E8FFE2D2616FE54" blockId="41.[189,1399,447,509]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
The species name refers to the location where the recently collected specimens were found: a dry river bank inhabited by a group of hippos that made access to the flowering 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDA8B035DC2FE702720FE54" box="[1008,1089,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Euclea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDA8B035DC2FE702720FE54" box="[1008,1089,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Euclea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bush particularly delicate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3036541FFDA8B035E8FFDB62168FC60" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="materials_examined">
