<subSubSection id="C3036541FFD88B015E8FFE9B2734FDD9" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD88B015E8FFE9B224EFE8B" blockId="43.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFD88B015E8FFE9B224EFE8B" bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015E8FFE9B224EFE8B" bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD88B015E8FFEA52106FE13" blockId="43.[188,1398,311,443]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
One of the female specimens from Orpen Gate of KNP shows a distinctly less downcurved and more elongate rostrum. This divergent phenotype exceeds the variability commonly observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015AECFEC82617FEDC" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[1246,1398,346,372]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015AECFEC82617FEDC" box="[1246,1398,346,372]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ebenacobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD88B015E8FFEEC2246FE30" box="[189,295,382,408]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015F49FEEF2160FE3F" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[379,513,381,407]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
in general and could indicate that several closely related species might exist in this species in its current concept.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD88B015E8FFE70222EFE54" blockId="43.[189,335,482,508]" box="[189,335,482,508]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFD88B015E8FFE70222EFE54" bold="true" box="[189,335,482,508]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015E8FFE70222EFE54" bold="true" box="[189,335,482,508]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Life history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD88B015E8FFD832734FDD9" blockId="43.[188,1399,529,626]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015E8FFD832147FD83" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,550,529,555]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippopotamorum" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015E8FFD832147FD83" box="[189,550,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ebenacobius hippopotamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD88B015C1DFD832180FD83" box="[559,737,529,555]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was collected on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015A06FD832665FD83" box="[1076,1284,529,555]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Euclea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015A06FD832665FD83" box="[1076,1284,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Euclea natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is probably its host plant. This species was collected in sympatry with 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015DFDFDA72711FDE6" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[975,1136,565,590]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015DFDFDA72711FDE6" box="[975,1136,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">E. rectirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD88B015A44FDA62642FDE6" box="[1142,1315,564,590]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
on this plant, although in smaller numbers. Adults were collected in July and October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
